1
00:00:01,043 --> 00:00:02,418
Yaga.

2
00:00:02,419 --> 00:00:04,421
What is that thing?

3
00:00:04,838 --> 00:00:06,781
Compared to other cursed techniques,

4
00:00:06,782 --> 00:00:11,010
artificial cursed corpses have
the ability to move on their own.

5
00:00:11,011 --> 00:00:13,846
However, a sorcerer must supply
and consume cursed energy

6
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:16,207
for them to move.

7
00:00:16,208 --> 00:00:18,419
But that thing's cursed energy
belongs to it.

8
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,437
And it can be self-replenished.

9
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:25,550
The higher-ups have recognized you
as a Special Grade Sorcerer

10
00:00:25,551 --> 00:00:29,112
and plan to officially order
your indefinite confinement.

11
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:33,908
Because if you intentionally
created that thing,

12
00:00:33,909 --> 00:00:37,746
it means you can easily create an army.

13
00:00:38,247 --> 00:00:40,374
Answer me, Yaga.

14
00:00:41,625 --> 00:00:47,005
Do you really not know
how that thing is made?

15
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,009
Yes.

16
00:00:52,094 --> 00:00:53,387
Masamichi.

17
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:56,430
Everyone's worried about you.

18
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:57,975
They say you're listless.

19
00:00:58,350 --> 00:00:59,768
Is that so?

20
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:04,188
So I bragged that

21
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:05,381
if you're listless,

22
00:01:05,382 --> 00:01:07,134
I'll be the one to cheer you up.

23
00:01:09,522 --> 00:01:10,731
I see.

24
00:01:11,634 --> 00:01:13,326
Aren't I a genius?

25
00:01:13,327 --> 00:01:14,871
You certainly are.

26
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:17,184
Takeru.

27
00:01:17,185 --> 00:01:19,979
I'm sorry, but I can't come home
for a while.

28
00:01:20,122 --> 00:01:22,398
Please tell everyone for me.

29
00:01:22,399 --> 00:01:24,217
Another business trip?

30
00:01:24,218 --> 00:01:26,971
Yes, a long one.

31
00:01:27,171 --> 00:01:28,404
Don't worry.

32
00:01:28,405 --> 00:01:31,617
Master Tengen will protect this forest.

33
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:35,512
Your mother will come to see you again.

34
00:01:36,889 --> 00:01:40,017
You'll be fine without me.

35
00:01:43,148 --> 00:01:44,524
Masamichi.

36
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:47,900
We'll be lonely without you.

37
00:01:53,155 --> 00:01:55,573
Are you sure, Kusakabe?

38
00:01:55,574 --> 00:01:58,618
Don't tell anyone I saved you.

39
00:01:58,619 --> 00:02:01,872
You were captured to lure Mr. Yaga out.

40
00:02:02,998 --> 00:02:05,459
I owe him one.

41
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,629
Come on, get going.

42
00:02:10,047 --> 00:02:11,757
Are you sure?

43
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:14,884
He's not your nephew.

44
00:02:14,885 --> 00:02:17,137
He's an entity with information
about your nephew.

45
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:19,872
You want me to stop obsessing
over someone who's dead.

46
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:23,585
Otherwise, I can't live in the future, right?

47
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:26,045
But...

48
00:02:26,046 --> 00:02:27,923
My sister

49
00:02:28,065 --> 00:02:31,360
can't live without Takeru now.

50
00:02:35,781 --> 00:02:39,826
Masamichi, she's my mother, isn't she?

51
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:43,580
That's right.
I'm impressed you recognized her.

52
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:47,793
I thought so.

53
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:51,755
Aren't I a genius?

54
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,853
Takeru...

55
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:11,942
I'm sorry...

56
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:13,926
I know.

57
00:03:13,927 --> 00:03:18,455
The existence of a fully independent
cursed corpse can't be made public.

58
00:03:18,456 --> 00:03:20,082
They can't live together.

59
00:03:20,284 --> 00:03:21,701
I'm sorry.

60
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:24,037
Why are you apologizing?

61
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:27,082
Thank you so much.

62
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,168
I mean it.

63
00:03:30,085 --> 00:03:31,545
Thank you so much.

64
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:35,781
Where are you going without
a cursed corpse?

65
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:37,283
Principal Yaga.

66
00:03:38,302 --> 00:03:39,887
I'm going to see my son.

67
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:45,541
I'll tell you the only way
you can survive.

68
00:03:45,542 --> 00:03:50,338
Tell me how to make a fully
independent artificial cursed corpse.

69
00:03:51,627 --> 00:03:55,047
Since Satoru left,
you've suddenly become more aggressive.

70
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:26,975
Principal.

71
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:30,795
I'll take it from here. You may leave.

72
00:04:30,796 --> 00:04:31,881
Yes, sir.

73
00:04:33,148 --> 00:04:35,049
First, I'll copy the information

74
00:04:35,050 --> 00:04:38,369
from the body and the soul.

75
00:04:38,370 --> 00:04:43,208
Then we input that information
into the core of the cursed corpse.

76
00:04:46,078 --> 00:04:48,396
But that's not enough.

77
00:04:48,397 --> 00:04:51,549
The cores of three souls
that are compatible

78
00:04:51,550 --> 00:04:53,826
must be placed into one cursed corpse,

79
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:58,082
so that the three souls can
keep observing each other.

80
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,991
By doing this,

81
00:04:59,992 --> 00:05:02,310
the souls will stabilize

82
00:05:02,311 --> 00:05:04,188
and form self-awareness.

83
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:06,873
Around three months after birth,

84
00:05:06,874 --> 00:05:09,567
they started replenishing
their cursed energy.

85
00:05:09,568 --> 00:05:14,698
Why are you telling me this now?

86
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:18,384
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

87
00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:20,805
Why didn't you want to live?

88
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:24,724
Because this is a curse.

89
00:05:24,725 --> 00:05:27,001
Principal Gakuganji.

90
00:05:27,002 --> 00:05:31,256
This is the curse I put on you.

91
00:05:35,252 --> 00:05:36,378
Masamichi!

92
00:05:46,722 --> 00:05:48,706
Why don't you fight?

93
00:05:48,707 --> 00:05:50,668
Don't you hate me?

94
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:54,188
Pandas don't get hung up
on things like that.

95
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:58,358
Besides, you and Masamichi
don't have a bad relationship.

96
00:05:59,193 --> 00:06:03,322
To me, you're just a dagger
that fell on the ground.

97
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:08,118
But you'd better remember one thing.

98
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:12,372
Even pandas cry.

99
00:06:30,432 --> 00:06:31,266
JUJUTSU KAISEN

100
00:06:53,247 --> 00:06:54,456
(JUJUTSU KAISEN THE CULLING GAME PART 1)

101
00:07:50,679 --> 00:07:54,415
Kinji Hakari is currently at the old
parking lot in Tochigi Prefecture.

102
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:57,986
He's making money as a bookmaker
for gambling tournaments.

103
00:07:57,987 --> 00:07:59,496
Gambling tournaments?

104
00:07:59,497 --> 00:08:02,066
It's where jujutsu sorcerers
fight each other.

105
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:03,860
So the gamblers are...

106
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:06,445
Basically, non-sorcerers.

107
00:08:06,979 --> 00:08:11,734
Doesn't that completely violate
Jujutsu Rule No. 8, "Secrecy"?

108
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:15,228
There must be curse users
among the participants.

109
00:08:15,229 --> 00:08:17,189
Be careful when taking action.

110
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:21,734
Why do we have to change clothes?

111
00:08:21,735 --> 00:08:24,846
Hakari was suspended because
of a dispute with the higher-ups.

112
00:08:24,847 --> 00:08:27,608
And he's currently violating
the Jujutsu Regulations.

113
00:08:27,925 --> 00:08:31,035
If he finds out we're from Jujutsu High,
he might just run away.

114
00:08:31,036 --> 00:08:33,789
Our relationship is like
a police officer and a thief.

115
00:08:33,931 --> 00:08:34,973
What?

116
00:08:35,432 --> 00:08:37,458
Are we considered part
of Jujutsu High right now?

117
00:08:37,459 --> 00:08:38,960
It's a bit delicate.

118
00:08:39,102 --> 00:08:41,837
But at least in Hakari's eyes, we are.

119
00:08:41,838 --> 00:08:44,239
Anyway, is he the type to
help us in the first place?

120
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,640
I don't know.

121
00:08:45,641 --> 00:08:48,519
After all, the upperclassmen
said he's scum.

122
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:53,188
But even Okkotsu said
he's stronger than him.

123
00:08:53,189 --> 00:08:55,810
In terms of combat power,
we definitely need his help.

124
00:08:55,811 --> 00:08:57,629
Go home, brats.

125
00:08:57,630 --> 00:09:00,049
This is not a place for you
to fool around.

126
00:09:00,186 --> 00:09:02,545
I'll count to three.
Turn around and leave.

127
00:09:02,546 --> 00:09:05,382
If you do anything else, I'll beat you up.

128
00:09:05,524 --> 00:09:06,883
I need money.

129
00:09:06,884 --> 00:09:09,466
Let me take part
in the gambling competition here.

130
00:09:12,135 --> 00:09:14,203
Rule number one.

131
00:09:14,204 --> 00:09:17,564
Don't mention the club.

132
00:09:17,565 --> 00:09:19,758
Answer me. Who told you?

133
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:21,993
I'll beat you up after you confess.

134
00:09:21,994 --> 00:09:23,629
I don't know his name.

135
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:24,714
Because I killed him.

136
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:27,383
It was about a month ago.

137
00:09:27,384 --> 00:09:29,744
Isn't there a good-for-nothing
who just acts tough?

138
00:09:29,745 --> 00:09:32,330
Kondo disappeared a month ago.

139
00:09:33,574 --> 00:09:35,766
I can fill his shoes.

140
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:39,253
Or I can steamroll up in front
of the bookmaker.

141
00:09:39,254 --> 00:09:40,454
I see.

142
00:09:40,455 --> 00:09:43,024
If we ask to meet him right away,
he'll be more cautious.

143
00:09:43,025 --> 00:09:46,052
- And he can't reveal he knows Hakari.
- Yes. No, there's no proof.

144
00:09:46,053 --> 00:09:47,971
- I'll just keep my mouth shut.
- Are you sure?

145
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:50,132
That's enough.

146
00:09:50,966 --> 00:09:52,992
The boss allowed them to enter.

147
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:55,579
We'll send him in as today's seed.

148
00:09:55,721 --> 00:09:56,954
However...

149
00:09:56,955 --> 00:09:58,706
It's going to be the other kid.

150
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:02,126
Just as I wanted.

151
00:10:02,127 --> 00:10:04,862
Itadori is more suitable for
the competition than me.

152
00:10:04,863 --> 00:10:06,698
No, I'll go.

153
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:09,359
The boss said he doesn't
like the look of you.

154
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:11,952
Forget it if you don't accept.

155
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:15,699
Understood. Let's do that.

156
00:10:16,093 --> 00:10:17,744
Fushiguro, isn't that too dangerous?

157
00:10:17,745 --> 00:10:19,414
That's too much of a bluff.

158
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:20,912
It's not that bad.

159
00:10:21,622 --> 00:10:23,206
Since a curse user is involved,

160
00:10:23,207 --> 00:10:26,067
there should be some staff rotation.

161
00:10:26,068 --> 00:10:27,177
Anyway,

162
00:10:27,178 --> 00:10:29,222
yes, he's here.

163
00:10:29,311 --> 00:10:32,263
Since he saw us
through the monitor just now,

164
00:10:32,264 --> 00:10:35,125
there's a high chance Hakari is there.

165
00:10:35,126 --> 00:10:38,054
Itadori, you'll investigate
from the inside.

166
00:10:38,055 --> 00:10:41,207
I'll sneak into that parking lot
during that time...

167
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,066
Probably.

168
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:43,142
Probably?

169
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,102
They're probably letting me
do whatever I want.

170
00:10:45,103 --> 00:10:46,712
If they find out I've snuck in,

171
00:10:46,713 --> 00:10:48,006
they'll lose trust in me.

172
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:50,359
And I'll lose my chance to contact Hakari.

173
00:10:50,776 --> 00:10:54,053
Then we'll have to use brute force.

174
00:10:54,054 --> 00:10:56,414
That's the real last resort.

175
00:10:56,415 --> 00:10:57,749
After all,

176
00:10:57,950 --> 00:11:01,227
we're asking for his help.

177
00:11:01,228 --> 00:11:04,064
We must avoid any situation
that might affect our future.

178
00:11:04,748 --> 00:11:05,606
To be honest,

179
00:11:05,607 --> 00:11:08,151
I don't think I should
make a move tonight.

180
00:11:08,277 --> 00:11:10,929
But I don't want to waste any time
before Tsumiki's deadline

181
00:11:10,930 --> 00:11:12,724
to declare for the Culling Game.

182
00:11:13,799 --> 00:11:14,949
Currently...

183
00:11:14,950 --> 00:11:17,119
It's 5 p.m. on the 10th.

184
00:11:17,261 --> 00:11:19,161
Nine days left until the deadline?

185
00:11:19,162 --> 00:11:22,415
It took us longer
to get here than expected.

186
00:11:22,975 --> 00:11:24,667
So I'll sneak in tonight too.

187
00:11:24,668 --> 00:11:26,295
I'll investigate Hakari in secret.

188
00:11:26,895 --> 00:11:29,046
If things go south, I'll stop.

189
00:11:29,047 --> 00:11:30,673
That's why I said "probably".

190
00:11:30,816 --> 00:11:31,817
Got it.

191
00:11:33,861 --> 00:11:35,428
There are two rules.

192
00:11:35,429 --> 00:11:38,057
"No running away" and
"No cursed techniques".

193
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:39,056
Why?

194
00:11:39,057 --> 00:11:42,125
I don't mind
if the opponent uses cursed techniques.

195
00:11:42,126 --> 00:11:44,044
Most of the customers are non-sorcerers.

196
00:11:44,246 --> 00:11:45,688
They can't see cursed techniques.

197
00:11:45,689 --> 00:11:48,466
They won't understand the fight,
and the atmosphere won't be lively.

198
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:49,968
What about "No running away"?

199
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:53,696
It means "fight within sight
of the customers".

200
00:11:53,697 --> 00:11:56,015
It's all about the customers.

201
00:11:56,016 --> 00:11:58,477
Of course. We're doing business.

202
00:11:59,261 --> 00:12:00,596
What kind of person is the boss?

203
00:12:02,014 --> 00:12:03,140
Are you curious?

204
00:12:03,765 --> 00:12:04,892
Kind of.

205
00:12:05,644 --> 00:12:07,003
You'll find out when you meet him.

206
00:12:07,004 --> 00:12:08,214
Can I meet him?

207
00:12:09,438 --> 00:12:11,422
There are two types of matches.

208
00:12:11,423 --> 00:12:13,843
Today's tournament is a "Real Match".

209
00:12:13,984 --> 00:12:15,676
The other is a "Fake Match".

210
00:12:15,677 --> 00:12:17,971
Of course, the boss writes the script.

211
00:12:18,488 --> 00:12:19,764
If you put on a good show,

212
00:12:19,765 --> 00:12:21,225
he might seek you out.

213
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:25,269
So, all I have to do is go wild, right?

214
00:12:25,270 --> 00:12:27,397
That makes things a lot simpler.

215
00:12:37,049 --> 00:12:40,052
That's your opponent.

216
00:12:42,721 --> 00:12:46,016
I was shocked when I first saw him too.

217
00:12:47,518 --> 00:12:49,937
He truly is a tourist attraction.

218
00:12:52,144 --> 00:12:54,462
All right, tonight's match
is about to begin.

219
00:12:54,463 --> 00:12:57,466
Gachinko Fight Club Tournament!

220
00:12:57,694 --> 00:13:01,239
I, your familiar host, John Bobi,
will be broadcasting.

221
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:04,475
Let's introduce tonight's
super exciting contestants.

222
00:13:04,476 --> 00:13:08,229
A sudden assassin appears,
an unexpected guest emerges.

223
00:13:08,372 --> 00:13:13,210
The dangerous and thrilling
Fireball Boy, Yuji Itadori.

224
00:13:13,545 --> 00:13:16,028
He stands like a Panda, sits like a Panda.

225
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:18,698
He walks exactly like a Panda.

226
00:13:18,841 --> 00:13:22,094
Here comes Panda!

227
00:13:22,803 --> 00:13:24,328
(ARENA)
Come on, place your bets!

228
00:13:24,329 --> 00:13:27,665
(ARENA)
Have you placed your bets? No more bets!

229
00:13:27,808 --> 00:13:30,685
I can feel the excitement fading.

230
00:13:30,686 --> 00:13:32,753
Why is that, Kinji?

231
00:13:32,754 --> 00:13:34,214
Whether "luck" is good or bad,

232
00:13:34,356 --> 00:13:36,191
you won't know until you try, right?

233
00:13:36,764 --> 00:13:39,552
A bet where the outcome is
obvious from the start is boring.

234
00:13:39,553 --> 00:13:43,641
Among rogue sorcerers, few can beat Panda.

235
00:13:44,908 --> 00:13:46,993
- This has to be the best match
- I don't think so.

236
00:13:46,994 --> 00:13:48,811
in my live broadcasting career!

237
00:13:48,812 --> 00:13:50,939
(ARENA)

238
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,502
Panda, have you met Hakari yet?

239
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,171
Not yet.

240
00:13:57,921 --> 00:13:58,755
(POKE)

241
00:14:02,009 --> 00:14:04,535
Even though we know each other,
he wasn't wary of me.

242
00:14:04,536 --> 00:14:05,954
But he avoided seeing me.

243
00:14:06,305 --> 00:14:07,347
(POKE...)

244
00:14:07,848 --> 00:14:10,517
(WHOA!)

245
00:14:10,893 --> 00:14:14,563
Another problem is the cursed technique
of the other third-year.

246
00:14:23,614 --> 00:14:26,300
You're hiding your identity
as a Jujutsu High student, right?

247
00:14:26,301 --> 00:14:27,343
Yes.

248
00:14:28,952 --> 00:14:30,061
Very good.

249
00:14:30,062 --> 00:14:31,480
You know what to do next, right?

250
00:14:38,694 --> 00:14:43,032
This is definitely the best match
in my live broadcasting career!

251
00:14:43,033 --> 00:14:46,203
Even though I've only been
an announcer for half a month.

252
00:14:50,891 --> 00:14:51,725
(POKE)

253
00:14:53,477 --> 00:14:54,311
(POKE)

254
00:14:55,729 --> 00:14:56,563
(POKE)

255
00:14:57,397 --> 00:15:00,067
(POKE...)

256
00:15:04,488 --> 00:15:05,322
(POKE)

257
00:15:11,537 --> 00:15:15,249
The winner is Itadori!

258
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:18,901
His punch is too strong. I can't move!

259
00:15:18,902 --> 00:15:23,089
Animal rights groups won't stand for this!

260
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:24,966
Such lame acting.

261
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:28,411
After the tournament,
bring Itadori to the rooftop.

262
00:15:28,412 --> 00:15:29,328
What?

263
00:15:29,329 --> 00:15:30,496
He's going to win all the matches anyway.

264
00:15:30,497 --> 00:15:33,624
Besides, he deliberately
made stereoscopic moves

265
00:15:33,625 --> 00:15:35,776
to attract the audience upstairs.

266
00:15:35,777 --> 00:15:37,904
I think I can write a good script.

267
00:15:38,105 --> 00:15:39,398
Didn't I always say,

268
00:15:40,594 --> 00:15:43,764
strike while the iron is hot? Get it?

269
00:15:44,194 --> 00:15:46,470
That seems foolish. Let's not do that.

270
00:15:46,471 --> 00:15:47,329
Okay.

271
00:15:47,330 --> 00:15:49,875
But what about the other kid?

272
00:15:50,075 --> 00:15:52,393
Continue to keep an eye on him.

273
00:15:52,394 --> 00:15:54,605
I'll send Kirara
to join the security later.

274
00:15:55,497 --> 00:15:57,648
I like this excitement.

275
00:15:57,649 --> 00:15:59,842
The last time I was this excited

276
00:15:59,843 --> 00:16:03,412
was when my ex-girlfriend
went on a crazy installment spree.

277
00:16:03,413 --> 00:16:05,456
Don't talk about your ex-girlfriend!

278
00:16:05,716 --> 00:16:07,009
(KINJI HAKARI,JUJUTSU HIGH THIRD-YEAR
KIRARA HOSHI,JUJUTSU HIGH THIRD-YEAR)

279
00:16:08,802 --> 00:16:10,261
I see.

280
00:16:10,262 --> 00:16:13,598
It looks like Itadori has a chance
to meet Hakari.

281
00:16:13,599 --> 00:16:15,016
Panda,

282
00:16:15,017 --> 00:16:17,603
why haven't you met Hakari yet?

283
00:16:18,103 --> 00:16:20,338
I know where he is.

284
00:16:20,339 --> 00:16:22,532
He's in the control room on the roof.

285
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,911
But I just can't get close.

286
00:16:25,694 --> 00:16:26,928
You can't get close?

287
00:16:26,929 --> 00:16:30,464
No matter how long I walk
towards the door, I can't get any closer.

288
00:16:30,465 --> 00:16:33,760
It's similar to Satoru's cursed technique.

289
00:16:33,952 --> 00:16:36,871
It's probably Kirara's cursed technique?

290
00:16:36,872 --> 00:16:38,289
Kirara?

291
00:16:38,290 --> 00:16:41,000
Isn't the other third-year a boy?

292
00:16:41,001 --> 00:16:42,276
He is a boy.

293
00:16:42,277 --> 00:16:43,252
That phenomenon,

294
00:16:43,253 --> 00:16:46,714
does it only happen when Kirara
is in the control room?

295
00:16:46,715 --> 00:16:48,074
I don't know.

296
00:16:48,075 --> 00:16:50,818
I thought that rather than chasing him
and letting him get away,

297
00:16:50,819 --> 00:16:52,803
I should be a panda
that attracts tourists.

298
00:16:52,804 --> 00:16:54,973
I'm glad you two are here.

299
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:58,167
Do you think Itadori can convince him?

300
00:16:58,168 --> 00:16:59,627
It won't be easy.

301
00:16:59,770 --> 00:17:02,213
But I think it's just a matter of time.

302
00:17:02,214 --> 00:17:06,859
Itadori is cheerful and naturally likable,
so he should get along with Hakari.

303
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:09,086
But he's not good at lying, right?

304
00:17:09,087 --> 00:17:10,738
It's not that he's not good at it.

305
00:17:10,739 --> 00:17:13,450
He's more like someone who wouldn't
even think of lying in the first place.

306
00:17:13,592 --> 00:17:14,700
So?

307
00:17:14,701 --> 00:17:17,662
The moment Itadori enters
the control room,

308
00:17:17,663 --> 00:17:19,997
we must immediately sneak in
and neutralize their base

309
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:22,835
to buy them time to talk.

310
00:17:22,976 --> 00:17:24,126
No, this method...

311
00:17:24,127 --> 00:17:25,044
Don't worry.

312
00:17:25,045 --> 00:17:26,963
We'll just have them take a nap.

313
00:17:26,964 --> 00:17:29,715
I've already mapped out
the camera locations and blind spots.

314
00:17:29,716 --> 00:17:31,384
How many guards are there?

315
00:17:31,385 --> 00:17:32,760
Four at the entrance.

316
00:17:32,761 --> 00:17:35,305
Two on each floor, except the rooftop.

317
00:17:37,948 --> 00:17:39,282
This might work.

318
00:17:39,476 --> 00:17:42,461
My only concern is Kirara's
cursed technique.

319
00:17:42,462 --> 00:17:44,547
That can't be helped.

320
00:17:44,690 --> 00:17:48,609
If he teleports Itadori away
or calls his comrades,

321
00:17:48,610 --> 00:17:51,029
we'll give up on persuading Hakari.

322
00:17:51,339 --> 00:17:54,824
Yuji, you're only a first-year
high schooler? So young.

323
00:17:54,825 --> 00:17:55,826
Yuji...

324
00:17:56,201 --> 00:17:58,412
Kinji repeated a year
in middle school, you know.

325
00:17:58,996 --> 00:18:01,039
You look happy.

326
00:18:01,832 --> 00:18:02,708
I am.

327
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:06,211
It's been a while since Kinji
has been so zealous.

328
00:18:07,296 --> 00:18:08,779
You know,

329
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:11,449
I love a passionate Kinji.

330
00:18:16,471 --> 00:18:18,039
Itadori.

331
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,792
If someone told you,

332
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:22,852
"You can earn a million yen a month
by doing something for an hour a day,"

333
00:18:22,853 --> 00:18:25,022
would you believe it?

334
00:18:26,064 --> 00:18:27,315
What?

335
00:18:27,316 --> 00:18:29,842
It depends on what it is.

336
00:18:29,843 --> 00:18:31,761
But if you want to know
what that "something" is,

337
00:18:31,762 --> 00:18:34,974
you have to pay 200,000 yen
for the information first.

338
00:18:36,825 --> 00:18:38,242
How could I believe that?

339
00:18:38,243 --> 00:18:40,703
Exactly. It's just as you feel.

340
00:18:40,704 --> 00:18:43,208
It's a typical scam.

341
00:18:43,209 --> 00:18:45,444
The con artist presents himself as rich.

342
00:18:45,445 --> 00:18:48,949
He sells a way to get rich
and makes money that way.

343
00:18:49,129 --> 00:18:51,464
If you think about it,
it's obviously a scam.

344
00:18:51,465 --> 00:18:54,300
But there are a lot of idiots
who get scammed.

345
00:18:54,301 --> 00:18:55,551
Why?

346
00:18:55,552 --> 00:18:58,137
It's all because of "zeal."

347
00:18:58,138 --> 00:18:59,138
Zeal?

348
00:18:59,139 --> 00:19:02,433
Both the con artist and the victim
have the "zeal"

349
00:19:02,434 --> 00:19:05,979
to "turn their lives around here."

350
00:19:06,897 --> 00:19:10,107
Once a person is blinded by "zeal,"
they make poor judgments.

351
00:19:10,108 --> 00:19:14,153
But without "zeal,"
you can't even fall in love.

352
00:19:14,154 --> 00:19:16,490
And I love "zeal."

353
00:19:17,282 --> 00:19:19,659
There's a more direct way
of communicating "zeal"...

354
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:21,161
Do you know what it is?

355
00:19:22,162 --> 00:19:23,372
Is it gambling?

356
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:29,585
You really get it.

357
00:19:29,586 --> 00:19:32,088
Life is a gamble.

358
00:19:32,089 --> 00:19:35,550
A lot of women dumped me
because they hated gambling.

359
00:19:35,551 --> 00:19:38,011
But they got it all wrong.

360
00:19:38,971 --> 00:19:41,722
In this society, the first to be
eliminated are those who can't bluff

361
00:19:41,723 --> 00:19:45,434
and those who don't know
when to quit while they're ahead.

362
00:19:45,435 --> 00:19:48,604
Who in the world doesn't gamble?

363
00:19:48,605 --> 00:19:51,732
It's not gambling that they hate.

364
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:54,485
It's "defeat" and "disillusion."

365
00:19:54,486 --> 00:19:57,446
Some people just want
to live a peaceful life.

366
00:19:57,447 --> 00:19:59,992
I don't care about those people.

367
00:20:00,742 --> 00:20:03,661
I love "zeal."

368
00:20:03,662 --> 00:20:05,413
"Zeal" is a "gamble."

369
00:20:05,414 --> 00:20:07,648
"Gambling" is "life."

370
00:20:07,649 --> 00:20:09,901
And "love" is "domination."

371
00:20:10,586 --> 00:20:12,528
In the future,
with the Gachinko Fight Club,

372
00:20:12,529 --> 00:20:15,615
I'm going to dominate
this country's "passion."

373
00:20:15,815 --> 00:20:17,800
The existence of cursed spirits
is widely known now.

374
00:20:17,801 --> 00:20:19,660
The Jujutsu Headquarters
can barely function.

375
00:20:19,661 --> 00:20:22,247
It's a good opportunity for me
to expand my business.

376
00:20:22,890 --> 00:20:24,766
I'm going to eliminate all obstacles.

377
00:20:24,909 --> 00:20:27,143
While the Jujutsu Regulations
are being revised,

378
00:20:27,144 --> 00:20:30,355
I'll use this opportunity to get
the fight club officially acknowledged.

379
00:20:31,148 --> 00:20:32,924
In short,

380
00:20:32,925 --> 00:20:35,177
I need a good pawn now.

381
00:20:36,486 --> 00:20:37,738
Itadori.

382
00:20:38,614 --> 00:20:41,742
Do you want to indulge in my "passion"?

383
00:20:42,910 --> 00:20:45,370
Bookie, I'd like to discuss--

384
00:20:57,716 --> 00:21:00,135
Itadori, do you want something to drink?

385
00:21:00,969 --> 00:21:03,513
Anything is fine, except alcohol.

386
00:21:03,514 --> 00:21:05,848
What? You can't hold your liquor?

387
00:21:05,849 --> 00:21:08,142
It's not about that. I'm a minor.

388
00:21:08,143 --> 00:21:10,628
I didn't think you'd care about that.

389
00:21:10,629 --> 00:21:13,632
You know what?
Satoru Gojo can't hold his liquor either.

390
00:21:13,774 --> 00:21:16,175
Who's Gojo?

391
00:21:16,176 --> 00:21:18,928
And you said "either." I didn't...

392
00:21:19,071 --> 00:21:20,280
Hey.

393
00:21:28,872 --> 00:21:32,400
What sorcerer hasn't heard of Satoru Gojo?

394
00:21:32,401 --> 00:21:34,260
Why are you pretending not to know?

395
00:21:34,261 --> 00:21:35,637
You...

396
00:21:42,177 --> 00:21:44,054
Are you from Jujutsu High?

397
00:21:51,128 --> 00:21:52,546
Listen, I'm...

398
00:21:53,021 --> 00:21:54,981
Wait, listen...

399
00:21:54,982 --> 00:21:55,898
Listen...

400
00:21:55,899 --> 00:21:58,442
Kirara is calling from his phone.

401
00:21:58,443 --> 00:22:00,779
It's a sign that something is wrong.

402
00:22:03,115 --> 00:22:04,031
Hear me out!

403
00:22:04,032 --> 00:22:05,283
I won't!

404
00:22:05,284 --> 00:22:06,963
It's because I've cooled down.

405
00:22:06,964 --> 00:22:09,967
(EPISODE 52 ZEAL)

406
00:23:40,671 --> 00:23:42,296
If I can persuade him somehow,

407
00:23:42,297 --> 00:23:44,131
negotiations with Hakari
will go more smoothly.

408
00:23:44,132 --> 00:23:45,258
Wait, Kirara!

409
00:23:45,259 --> 00:23:46,300
Stay out of this.

410
00:23:46,301 --> 00:23:49,136
You have to tell me right here!

411
00:23:49,137 --> 00:23:50,997
Please. We don't have much time.

412
00:23:50,998 --> 00:23:51,973
Kinji is in danger.

413
00:23:51,974 --> 00:23:55,000
(NEXT EPISODE, PARTS)
Kinji is in danger.

